content:
When Queue Management is enabled, supervisors can reassign agents to contact center groups on the fly. For example, if a queue gets swamped with calls and agents are running at capacity, a supervisor can reassign a group of agents from another queue.

To change groups: 
Manage Queues Membership
AND
Manage Users

This feature is available with Service Cloud Voice with Amazon Connect, Partner Telephony from Amazon Connect, or Partner Telephony.

When changes are made to a Salesforce contact center group, those changes are also updated in the associated Amazon Connect routing profile. 

To see the Change Groups button in Omni Supervisor, your admin must:
Enable Queue Management
Add Change Groups to the actions in the supervisor configuration assigned to you

In the Agents tab of Omni Supervisor, click Change Groups.
Select the agents that you want to reassign.
Select their new group.

All affected agents receive an email about the change. To apply the change, each agent must set their Omni-Channel status to offline, and then back to any available status. If a change canâ€™t be applied, check your email for the details.
title: Reassigning Agents to Contact Center Groups
